<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="4" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5169: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>)
                                to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-07T13:00:00+08:00">May 7, 1932—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 7—10:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>227. At meeting of Joint Commission today I was unanimously elected
                            chairman. Japanese reported withdrawals of troops from certain areas to
                            be effective before 9th. Chinese announced that Peiping police are due
                            here about the 9th and will take over policing.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Legation and Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>